00:23:53,798 --> 00:24:01,726
by the Blessed One, which cannot be stopped by any ascetic or Brahmin or deva or mara or brahma or anyone in that world.

188
00:24:02,346 --> 00:24:22,067
Thus, at that moment, at that instant, at that second, the cry spread as far as the Brahma world, and this ten-thousand-fold world system shook, quaked and trembled, and an immeasurable, glorious radiance appeared in the world, surpassing the divine majesty of the devas.

189
00:24:23,261 --> 00:24:29,769
Then the Blessed One uttered this inspired utterance, Kondanya has indeed understood.

190
00:24:30,250 --> 00:24:32,513
Kondanya has indeed understood.

191
00:24:32,973 --> 00:24:38,260
And in this way, the Venerable Kondanya acquired the name of Anya Kondanya.

192
00:24:38,780 --> 00:24:40,963
Kondanya, the one who knows.

193
00:24:43,487 --> 00:24:52,999
So that's a lovely poetic remembrance of the effect of turning the wheel of the Dhamma for us poor human beings.

